    "lag_vs_N_tension": "Amplitude rises toward flotation (corr(rel,ln amp)<0), as the master curve predicts. But the baseline cavity model predicts the discrete lag also RISES toward flotation, whereas these n=3 lags trend the opposite way (driven by the marginal Rutford 2.86-sigma point). So the lag-vs-N sign is an OPEN discriminator: more in-band detections are needed to settle whether lag grows or shrinks toward flotation."
