  "verdict": "Closed-form s_N(N) master curve verified to 1.4e-04 vs the repo's numeric s_N; |s_N|->3.00 well-grounded and diverges as N_c/(N-N_c) at N_c=0.060 MPa. The two-parameter law is INVERTIBLE: a natural drainage-step population recovers the flotation threshold N_c to a few percent (robustly: 0.4% at 10% amplitude noise), while m is degenerate with f far from flotation (14%). The same N_c fold implies a critical-slowing-down early-warning signal (rising velocity variance + AC1) toward ungrounding (Kendall tau var=0.54, AC1=0.55)."
